-- Djakovic, Norway’s Kongsberg Sign Agreement on Weapon Stations
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2012-10-12T12:27:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-12/djakovic-norway-s-kongsberg-sign-agreement-on-weapon-stations.html
Djuro Djakovic d.d. ,  Croatia ’s
largest heavy-vehicle maker, signed an agreement with Norway’s
Kongsberg Defence & Aerospace AS to produce jointly and sell
medium-caliber remote weapon stations or RWS.  The agreement, that was signed today in Kongsberg, Norway,
would allow Djakovic to be the main seller for the weapon, the
company said in a statement to the  Zagreb stock exchange .  Djakovic is based in Slavonski Brod, eastern Croatia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  